Hello!

I was wondering if it is possible to connect cameras that are being run on a raspberry pi to the elastic dashboard by Team 353. We followed the steps on slides 12-14 on this slideshow (FRCVision: Using a Raspberry Pi for Vision - Google Slides) and got the cameras working on a browser, but we do not know how to put the cameras into the elastic dashboard, if it is even possible. We know that we can use the cameras directly with the roborio in Elastic, and have been for the past few competitions, but the quality of the video was so bad it was essentially unusable. We aren’t doing anything fancy, like with AprilTags, only sending a video stream to a dashboard.

We are trying to avoid using SmartDashboard or Shuffleboard, since those are getting discontinued soon, and we will probably be shifting to LABView next year, but that will likely take a while.

Thanks!
348 Programming Team

Yes, it is actually possible if my knowledge is correct.

The way you need to do it is by starting the CameraServer in your robot, it’s a simple class you can find by searching a little bit into the shuffleboard docs. (Sorry couldn’t find it).

After this, Elastic should recognise you want to add a cammera display and into the “Add Widget” section you should be able to see the source or even search for it and add it into the dashboard.

If you’re using WPILibPi, if you set the team number in WPILibPi, it will publish the camera information to NT so they’ll show up in the Elastic camera list. You can use OutlineViewer to double-check that the Pi is connecting to NT and the camera information is there.
